narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you need your language credit then its useful to improve your fluency and also learn about Spanish speaking countries.
great spanish course, especially if you have just taken L1

Much harder and much more work than 110. Make sure to do well and every assignment. Organized better than 110. I took it with Tortora she was amazing and very kind and helpful. However, she graded a bit harder. I heard from other students that Ortega is an easier grader. Your welcome!
Great course and great professor! If you want to enjoy a spanish class, take this section. Professor Trtora is the best and she will help you out so much.
A lot of work but rewarding if you want to learn spanish
Challenging and a lot of work

Provides a solid foundation of Spanish. However, the workload is very large; took me hours each night to finish the variety of types of homework, as well as to study for assessments that take place at least weekly.
Yes i would recommend although you have to be committed to putting effort in everyday. Its a great language to get your requirement done.
